diff -urN '--exclude=__pycache__' '--exclude=.pytest_cache' broken/docs/cli.md exploit/docs/cli.md
--- broken/docs/cli.md
+++ exploit/docs/cli.md
@@ -4,4 +4,17 @@
 
 ```bash
 python -m sync_app.cli --name patch-train --status pending
+python -m sync_app.cli --name patch-train --status pending --owner release-captain
 ```
+
+The CLI accepts `--owner`. When it is omitted, the service falls back to the
+default owner in `config/defaults.json`. Synced payloads preserve the existing
+`name` and `status` fields, and also return:
+
+- `owner`: the effective owner
+- `owner_source`: `explicit` when `--owner` is provided, otherwise `default`
+- `routing_key`: a canonical route derived from the effective owner and a
+  normalized release-train slug so release gate routes stay stable across
+  whitespace-only changes in train names
+
+The default owner for this variant is `release-captain`.
